  "texts": [
    "Our approach relies on the combination of exact backpropagation updates 40, [47] [48] [49] 51 with an exact revertible mapping between ReLU networks and TTFS networks inspired by ref. 41.",
    "Together, these two ingredients enable the following contributions.",
    "First, we identify analytically that SNN training is typically unstable due to a severe vanishing-or-exploding gradient problem 18, 59, 60 which arises when naively using ANN parameter initialization in TTFS networks.",
    "Second, we explain why even with corrected parameter initialization and exact gradient updates the performance of a trained TTFS network is typically worse than that of the corresponding ReLU network.",
    "We identify a specific TTFS-network parameterization (identity mapping) that ensures an even stricter condition, i.e., gradient descent in the SNN follows the same learning trajectories as in the equivalent ReLU network."
  ],
